1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:04,833
I was put alone in a
room at the Dawasa Center

2
00:00:06,708 --> 00:00:08,375
From morning until evening

3
00:00:09,375 --> 00:00:15,041
Later they put me in a
car — me and three others

4
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:17,458
They seated us in the car

5
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:20,041
They shackled our hands
and blindfolded our eyes

6
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:23,541
And they covered us so
we couldn’t see the place

7
00:00:23,583 --> 00:00:25,041
And we were
transferred to a house

8
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:29,250
Interviewer: Was the interrogation
and torture carried out in that house?

9
00:00:29,250 --> 00:00:29,833
Yes

10
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,625
Alright, continue the story

11
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,041
We were transferred
there, to the house

12
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:38,541
Those others — I didn’t
know what their charge was

13
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,791
And my charge was theft, so they
brought me and put me in the room

14
00:00:42,458 --> 00:00:44,625
And they started
interrogating me

15
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:47,625
About how I’d entered,
what I took, and what I did

16
00:00:49,541 --> 00:00:53,583
I stayed two to three
days in the house

17
00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:55,833
Then I was transferred
afterwards to <i>Qaimaqam</i>

18
00:00:57,166 --> 00:01:02,791
I stayed for about a week,
maybe eight days, at the <i>Qaimaqam</i>

19
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:05,083
Or a week, roughly
ten days in total

20
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:09,375
I left there, and they also
brought me before a judge there

21
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:12,833
He asked me about my
charge too, and I said–Theft

22
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:16,125
I heard sounds of
flogging and beating

23
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:22,083
When I went in to see him
they took me back again

24
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:25,875
When I entered, he was sitting
behind me and I was sitting like this now

25
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:27,708
I was also sitting on a chair

26
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:29,458
And he sat behind
me asking questions

27
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,916
But he was lying on a bed

28
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:38,000
He asked me a
number of questions

29
00:01:38,541 --> 00:01:41,000
About my charge

30
00:01:41,041 --> 00:01:42,291
And I answered him

31
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:44,208
After that they took
me back to the hall

32
00:01:46,541 --> 00:01:49,416
They brought me into a large hall
that had once been for weddings

33
00:01:51,041 --> 00:01:53,916
At the <i>Qaimaqam</i>, it
used to be a wedding hall

34
00:01:54,958 --> 00:01:57,333
Huge, over there

35
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:02,125
I reckon it held
300 to 400 people

36
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:04,958
A large hall

37
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:08,416
With a stage for parties and
a spot for the bride and groom

38
00:02:08,458 --> 00:02:10,250
This hall was
turned into a prison

39
00:02:12,208 --> 00:02:16,208
So we stayed there, and whoever wanted to
walk could walk inside because it was so big

40
00:02:17,625 --> 00:02:19,541
They dressed us in
<i>dishdashas</i>, robes about this long

41
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:25,166
At prayer time anyone who wanted to
do <i>wudu</i> [ablution] could go to the toilets

42
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,291
There were three or four toilets

43
00:02:27,291 --> 00:02:29,375
Whoever went into the
toilets could take his time

44
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,333
The <i>Hisba</i> [religious police] car
came and they took us out of there

45
00:02:35,166 --> 00:02:37,583
They put us in the <i>Hisba</i> vehicle
and brought us here afterward
